Sergeant Louise Lucas was off-duty when she was hit by a bus in Swansea earlier this month . 
  She was pushing her daughter Olivia out of the path of the bus and saving her life . 
  Sgt Lucas was killed and her daughter escaped with minor injuries  . 
  Hundreds of police officers lined the roads for her funeral in Cardiff today . 
  Her husband Gavin said she would remain in his heart forever . 
 